name Opa's Cake
serves 1
desc Gugelhupf with raisins. Opa's birthday cake.
tags cake

# Preparation

- 250 g butter
- 250 g sugar
- 1 sachet vanilla sugar
- 4 eggs
- salt
Beat the butter until fluffy, then mix in the sugar, vanilla sugar, eggs and a pinch of salt.
-> butter mixture

- 375 g flour
- 125 g cornstarch
- 1 sachet baking powder
@nodep
Combine the dry ingredients.
-> flour mixture

- 125 ml milk
= butter mixture
= flour mixture
Fold the flour mixture into the butter mixture alternately with the milk. Add only enough
milk that the dough falls heavily from the spoon in thick ribbons.

- 350 g raisins
- breadcrumbs
Fold in the raisins. Transfer the dough to a greased Gugelhupf tin dusted with breadcrumbs.
Bake at 160°C fan for about 50 minutes.
